cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the security aspects of wireless networks, specifically key distribution and renewing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the modification of the scrambling circuits in the IEEE 802.11g standard, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The proposed technique is based on physical layer security principles, which involves the transmission of signals over a communication channel, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also presents a technique for automatic bootstrap and periodic renewing of the network key, which involves control systems and automation, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the modification of the scrambling circuits to achieve physical layer security, which involves signal processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
